def convert_to_datetime(date_str):
    # The format string corresponding to the input format
    date_format = "%a, %d %b %Y %H:%M:%S GMT"
    
    # Convert the string to a datetime object
    dt_object = datetime.strptime(date_str, date_format)
    
    return dt_object

for i in range(len(data)):

    data[i]['datetime'] = convert_to_datetime(datetime_string)

import pandas as pd
import pandas_datareader.data as pdr
from scipy.stats import zscore
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def fetch_and_standardize_mcsi(start, end):
    # Get the Michigan Consumer Sentiment Index from FRED
    michigan_sentiment = pdr.get_data_fred('UMCSENT', start=start, end=end)
    # Standardize the MCSI values
    michigan_sentiment['michigan sentiment index'] = zscore(michigan_sentiment)
    # Reset index to make 'datetime' a column
    michigan_sentiment.reset_index(inplace=True)
    return michigan_sentiment

def create_sentiment_index(df, timeframe, start_date=False, end_date=False):
    # Create dataframe with mean sentiment over chosen time frame
    index_df = df.groupby(df['datetime'].dt.to_period(timeframe)).agg({"sentiment": "mean"}) 
    
    # Date index now becomes a column (needed for plotting)
    index_df.reset_index(inplace=True)
    
    index_df["datetime"] = index_df["datetime"].apply(lambda p: p.to_timestamp())
    
    # Filter dataframe based on start and end date
    if start_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] >= start_date)]
    if end_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] <= end_date)]
    
    # Standardize the mean sentiment values
    index_df['standardized sentiment'] = zscore(index_df['sentiment'])
    
    # Compute final index by taking the standardized cumulative sum of mean sentiment
    index_df['NLP sentiment index'] = zscore(index_df['standardized sentiment'].cumsum().values)
    
    return index_df

def create_changes_index(df, timeframe, start_date=False, end_date=False):
    # Create dataframe with mean sentiment over chosen time frame
    index_df = df.groupby(df['datetime'].dt.to_period(timeframe)).agg({"sentiment": "mean"}) 
    
    # Date index now becomes a column (needed for plotting)
    index_df.reset_index(inplace=True)
    
    index_df["datetime"] = index_df["datetime"].apply(lambda p: p.to_timestamp())
    
    # Filter dataframe based on start and end date
    if start_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] >= start_date)]
    if end_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] <= end_date)]
    
    # Standardize the mean sentiment values
    index_df['NLP sentiment changes index'] = zscore(index_df['sentiment'])
    
    return index_df

def plot_multiple_indices(mcsi_params, sentiment_params):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    
    # Plot MCSI indices
    for params in mcsi_params:
        start, end, label = params
        mcsi_df = fetch_and_standardize_mcsi(start, end)
        plt.plot(mcsi_df["DATE"], mcsi_df['michigan sentiment index'], label=label, color='b')
        # plt.plot(mcsi_df["DATE"], mcsi_df["standardized"].diff, label=label, color='b')
    
    # Plot sentiment indices
    for params in sentiment_params:
        df, timeframe, start_date, end_date, label = params
        index_df = create_sentiment_index(df, timeframe, start_date, end_date)
        plt.plot(index_df["datetime"], index_df["NLP sentiment index"], label=label, color='g')
        #plt.plot(index_df["datetime"], index_df["sentiment index"].diff(), label=label, color='g')
    
    plt.title("Level Index Comparison")
    #plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel("Standardized Sentiment")
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
    
    


# Define MCSI parameters as tuples (start_date, end_date, label)
mcsi_params = [
    ("2013-01-01", "2024-04-01", "MCSI"),
]

# Define sentiment parameters as tuples (dataframe, timeframe, start_date, end_date, label)
sentiment_params = [
    (market_df, 'D', '2013-01-01', '2024-04-01', "MSI (Daily)"),
]

plot_multiple_indices(mcsi_params, sentiment_params)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import coint, adfuller
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

mcsi_sentiment = merged_df['michigan sentiment index']
msi_sentiment = merged_df['NLP sentiment index']

# Perform the ADF test on both series to confirm non-stationarity
adf_mcsi = adfuller(mcsi_sentiment)
adf_msi = adfuller(msi_sentiment)

# Perform the cointegration test
coint_test = coint(mcsi_sentiment, msi_sentiment)

# Compile results into a dataframe for clarity
results = {
    "ADF Statistic (MCSI)": adf_mcsi[0],
    "p-value (MCSI)": adf_mcsi[1],
    "ADF Statistic (MSI)": adf_msi[0],
    "p-value (MSI)": adf_msi[1],
    "Cointegration Statistic": coint_test[0],
    "p-value (Cointegration)": coint_test[1]
}

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results, index=["Value"])

# Display the results
print(results_df.T)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import coint, adfuller
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assume mcsi_sentiment and msi_sentiment are already defined

# Perform the ADF test on both series to confirm non-stationarity
adf_mcsi = adfuller(mcsi_sentiment)
adf_msi = adfuller(msi_sentiment)

# Perform the cointegration test
coint_test = coint(mcsi_sentiment, msi_sentiment)

# Calculate the differenced series
diff_mcsi_sentiment = mcsi_sentiment.diff().dropna()
diff_msi_sentiment = msi_sentiment.diff().dropna()

# Perform the ADF test on the differenced series
adf_diff_mcsi = adfuller(diff_mcsi_sentiment)
adf_diff_msi = adfuller(diff_msi_sentiment)

# Perform the cointegration test on the differenced series
coint_test_diff = coint(diff_mcsi_sentiment, diff_msi_sentiment)

# Compile results into a dataframe for clarity
results = {
    "ADF Statistic (MCSI)": adf_mcsi[0],
    "p-value (MCSI)": adf_mcsi[1],
    "ADF Statistic (MSI)": adf_msi[0],
    "p-value (MSI)": adf_msi[1],
    "ADF Statistic (Diff MCSI)": adf_diff_mcsi[0],
    "p-value (Diff MCSI)": adf_diff_mcsi[1],
    "ADF Statistic (Diff MSI)": adf_diff_msi[0],
    "p-value (Diff MSI)": adf_diff_msi[1],
    "Cointegration Statistic": coint_test[0],
    "p-value (Cointegration)": coint_test[1],
}

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results, index=["Value"])

# Display the results
round(results_df.T,3)

diff_msi_sentiment = msi_sentiment.diff().dropna()

def append_datetime(data):
    for entry in data:
        entry['datetime'] = convert_to_datetime(entry['timestamp'])
    return data

# Function to perform ADF test and print the results
def perform_adf_test(df, column_name, asset_name):
    result = adfuller(df[column_name].dropna())
    print(f"\nADF Test for {asset_name}:")
    print(f"ADF Statistic for {column_name}: {result[0]}")
    print(f"p-value: {result[1]}")
    for key, value in result[4].items():
        print(f'Critical Value {key}: {value}')

# Function to load data from a JSON file
def load_data(file_path):
    with open(file_path, 'r') as f:
        return json.load(f)

# Function to convert timestamp string to datetime
def convert_to_datetime(date_str):
    return datetime.strptime(date_str, "%a, %d %b %Y %H:%M:%S GMT")

# Function to append 'datetime' field to each entry in the dataset
def append_datetime(data):
    for entry in data:
        entry['datetime'] = convert_to_datetime(entry['timestamp'])
    return data

# Function to create sentiment index
def create_sentiment_index(dataframe, timeframe, start_date=False, end_date=False, crypto=False):
    if crypto:
        dataframe['datetime'] = dataframe['datetime'] - timedelta(hours=7)
    
    index_df = dataframe.groupby(dataframe['datetime'].dt.to_period(timeframe)).agg({"sentiment": "mean"})
    
    index_df.reset_index(inplace=True)
    index_df["datetime"] = index_df["datetime"].apply(lambda p: p.to_timestamp())
    
    if start_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] >= start_date)]
    if end_date:
        index_df = index_df[(index_df['datetime'] <= end_date)]
    
    index_df['standardized sentiment'] = zscore(index_df['sentiment'])
    index_df['sentiment index'] = zscore(index_df['standardized sentiment'].cumsum().values)
    
    return index_df

# Load and process each data file to append datetime
all_data = [append_datetime(load_data(file)) for file in file_list]

# Convert processed data dictionaries to DataFrames
all_dataframes = [pd.DataFrame(data) for data in all_data]

# Function to plot multiple indices
def plot_multiple_indices(dataframes, timeframes, start_dates=None, end_dates=None, labels=None):
    if start_dates is None:
        start_dates = [False] * len(dataframes)
    if end_dates is None:
        end_dates = [False] * len(dataframes)
    if labels is None:
        labels = [f'Index {i}' for i in range(len(dataframes))]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    
    for df, timeframe, start_date, end_date, label in zip(dataframes, timeframes, start_dates, end_dates, labels):
        index_df = create_sentiment_index(df, timeframe, start_date, end_date)
        plt.plot(index_df["datetime"], index_df["sentiment index"], label=label)
    
    plt.title("Sentiment Indices Comparison")
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylim(-3, 3)
    plt.ylabel("Sentiment Index")
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

# Define parameters
timeframes = ['M'] * len(all_dataframes)  # Monthly aggregation for all
start_dates = ['2018-01-01'] * len(all_dataframes)
end_dates = ['2023-04-01'] * len(all_dataframes)

# Plot all indices
plot_multiple_indices(all_dataframes, timeframes, start_dates, end_dates, labels)

def ff5_regression_hac(dataframe, ticker, start_date, end_date, market_df, ff5_data, include_market_sentiment=False, crypto=False, include_nothing=False):
    # Fetch prices and calculate returns
    prices = yf.download(ticker, start=start_date, end=end_date)
    prices['Return'] = prices['Adj Close'].pct_change().dropna()
    return_df = prices[['Return']].dropna()
    
    # Create sentiment indices
    asset_sentiment_df = create_sentiment_index(dataframe, 'D', start_date, end_date)[['datetime', 'standardized sentiment']]
    asset_sentiment_df.rename(columns={'standardized sentiment': 'asset sentiment'}, inplace=True)
    market_sentiment_df = create_sentiment_index(market_df, 'D', start_date, end_date)[['datetime', 'standardized sentiment']]
    market_sentiment_df.rename(columns={'standardized sentiment': 'market sentiment'}, inplace=True)
    sentiment_df = pd.merge(asset_sentiment_df, market_sentiment_df, on='datetime', how='inner')
    
    # Merge data for regression
    regression_data = return_df.merge(ff5_data, left_index=True, right_index=True)
    regression_data.reset_index(inplace=True)
    regression_data.rename(columns={'Date': 'datetime'}, inplace=True)
    regression_data = pd.merge(regression_data, sentiment_df, on='datetime', how='inner')
    
    # Define independent variables
    if include_market_sentiment:
        X = regression_data[['Mkt-RF', 'SMB', 'HML', 'RMW', 'CMA', 'asset sentiment', 'market sentiment']]
    elif include_nothing:
        X = regression_data[['Mkt-RF', 'SMB', 'HML', 'RMW', 'CMA']]
    else:
        X = regression_data[['Mkt-RF', 'SMB', 'HML', 'RMW', 'CMA', 'asset sentiment']]
    
    Y = regression_data['Return'] - regression_data['RF']
    X = sm.add_constant(X)
    model = sm.OLS(Y, X).fit()  

    # Calculate HAC standard errors
    hac_se = model.get_robustcov_results(cov_type='HAC', maxlags=4)

    return hac_se.summary()
    

# Example usage (you need to define market_df and ff5_data to use this function)
results = ff5_regression_hac(df, 'AAPL', '2013-01-01', '2024-04-01', market_df, ff5_data,include_market_sentiment=True)
print(results)
